	Lensless camera creates 3D images from single exposure | News Releases  | Optica
</title><meta name="description" content="Researchers have developed a camera that uses a thin microlens array and new image processing algorithms to capture 3D information about objects in a scene with a single exposure. The camera could be useful for a variety of applications such as industrial part inspection, gesture recognition and collecting data for 3D display systems." /> 
